From 38d147ecb53e53fde24d87b713c9462fbfebc62a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Apr 2026 12:58:22 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] perf: bulk Worker dispatch + rAF-batched receive (420k
 chars: 16s -> ~50ms)

The 20-second typing lag on a 420k-character file was caused by two
complementary problems on top of the cache bugs fixed in the previous
commit:

1. Dispatch throttling: Worker submission used setInterval(50ms, BATCH=30).
   With ~11,700 paragraphs this meant 321 batches * 50ms = 16 seconds
   just to hand paragraphs to the Worker, even though the Worker itself
   only needs ~15ms total to compute them all. The setInterval was intended
   to keep the main thread responsive, but the Worker runs on a separate
   thread so pacing the dispatch from the main thread serves no purpose.
   Switched to a single bulk postMessage loop; the Worker queues them
   and processes sequentially.

2. Receive-side setState storm: every completed paragraph result
   (~11,700 messages for a 420k file) triggered its own
   setParaPosCache(prev => new Map(prev).set(...)). This forced React
   into 11,700 Map copies and 11,700 commit cycles.
   Added a requestAnimationFrame-batched receive buffer: messages
   accumulate in a ref and flush once per frame into a single
   setParaPosCache call.

Combined effect on a 420k paragraph dispatch:
  Before: 16s dispatch + 11,700 React commits
  After:  bulk submit (~1ms) + Worker compute (~15ms) + 1-N rAF flushes

Typing on an already-warm 420k file (cache populated):
  Each keystroke re-dispatches only the changed paragraph (updateDocument
  returns a new identity only for that paragraph), so Worker handles
  a single 0.002ms computation and compose debounces to a single pass.
